ernmental or other entities at the communities by the United States in its operations at or near the communities;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"c","heading":null,"label":"c","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s2303/c","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s2303","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs2303%2Fc","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the opportunity for the residents of the communities to assume the obligations and privileges of local self-government; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"d","heading":null,"label":"d","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s2303/d","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s2303","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs2303%2Fd","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the encouragement of the construction of new homes at the communities.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]}
